msgid "<title>EPS</title>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:5895
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"EPS() returns the machine epsilon; this is the difference between 1 and the "
"next largest floating-point number. Because computers use a finite number of "
"digits, roundoff error is inherent (but usually insignificant) in all "
"calculations."
msgstr ""
"De Funkschoon EPS() gifft dat Reekner-Epsilon torüch. Dat is de Verscheel "
"twischen 1 un de nakamen gröttst Fleetkommatall. Wiel Reekners en ennen Tall "
"vun Nakommasteden bruukt, gifft dat bi't Reken jümmers Runnfehlers "
"(normalerwies ahn Utwarken)."

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:5900
#, no-c-format
msgid "EPS()"
msgstr "EPS()"

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:5906
#, no-c-format
msgid "On most systems, this returns 2^-52=2.2204460492503131e-16"
msgstr "Op de mehrsten Systemen gifft dit 2^-52=2.2204460492503131e-16 torüch"

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:5909
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"0.5*EPS() returns the \"unit round\"; this value is interesting because it "
"is the largest number x where (1+x)-1=0 (due to roundoff errors)."
msgstr ""
"0.5*EPS() gifft de Maschiennauigkeit \"unit round\" torüch. Disse Weert is "
"intressant, wiel dat de gröttste Tall x is, för de (1+x)-1=0 is (dör "
"Runnfehlers)."

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:5912
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "EPS() is so small that KSpread displays 1+eps() as 1"
msgid "EPS() is so small that &sheets; displays 1+eps() as 1"
msgstr "EPS() is so lütt, dat KSpread 1+eps() as 1 dorstellt"

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:5915
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Pick a number x between 0 and EPS(). Observe that 1+x rounds x to either 0 "
"or EPS() by using the equation (1+x)-1"
msgstr ""
"Söök en Tall x twischen 0 un EPS() ut. Beacht, dat x bi 1+x dör de Glieken "
"(1+x)-1 na 0 oder EPS() rundt warrt"

