#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:7576
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The AVERAGE() function calculates the average of all the values given as "
"parameters. You can calculate the average of a range AVERAGE(A1:B5) or a "
"list of values like AVERAGE(12;5;12.5)."
msgstr ""
"De Funkschoon AVERAGE() reekt den Dörsnitt vun all as Parameters angeven "
"Weerten ut. Een kann den Dörsnitt vun en Rebeet AVERAGE(A1:B5) oder en List "
"vun Weerten liek AVERAGE(12;5;12.5) utreken."

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:7581
#, no-c-format
msgid "AVERAGE(value;value;...)"
msgstr "AVERAGE(Weert;Weert;...)"

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:7592
#, no-c-format
msgid "AVERAGE(12;5;7) equals 8"
msgstr "AVERAGE(12;5;7) gifft \"8\" torüch"

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:7595
#, no-c-format
msgid "AVERAGE(12.5;2) equals 7.25"
msgstr "AVERAGE(12,5;2) gifft \"7,25\" torüch"

#. Tag: title
#: functions.docbook:7601
#, no-c-format
msgid "AVERAGEA"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:7602
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The AVERAGEA() calculates the average of the given arguments. Numbers, text "
"and logical values are included in the calculation too. If the cell contains "
"text or the argument evaluates to FALSE, it is counted as value zero (0). If "
"the argument evaluates to TRUE, it is counted as one (1). Note that empty "
"cells are not counted."
msgstr ""
"De Funkschoon AVERAGEA() reekt den Dörsnitt vun de angeven Parameters ut. "
"Tallen, Text un boolsch Weerten warrt ok inslaten. Wenn de Zell Text bargt "
"oder dat Resultaat \"falsch\" is, warrt de Weert as Null (0) tellt, un as "
"Een (1), wenn dat Argument \"wohr\" is. Beacht, dat leddig Zellen nich tellt "
"warrt."

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:7607
#, no-c-format
msgid "AVERAGEA(value;value;...)"
msgstr "AVERAGEA(Weert;Weert;...)"

