msgid "FIND"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:9564
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The FIND() function finds one text string (find_text) within another text "
"string (within_text) and returns the number of the starting point of "
"find_text, from the leftmost character of within_text."
msgstr ""
"De Funkschoon FIND() söcht en Tekenkeed (Sööktext) binnen en anner Tekenkeed "
"(binnen_dissen_Text) un gifft de Nummer vun de Startpositschoon vun "
"\"Sööktext\" vun dat sietste Teken vun \"binnen_dissen_Text\" ut."

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:9565
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Parameter start_num specifies the character at which to start the search. "
"The first character is character number 1. If start_num is omitted, it is "
"assumed to be 1."
msgstr ""
"De Parameter \"Startnummer\" leggt dat Startteken för de Söök fast. Dat "
"eerste Teken is Teken Nummer 1. Wenn \"Startnummer\" weglaten is, warrt "
"\"1\" vermoodt."

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:9566
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also use function SEARCH, but unlike SEARCH, FIND is case-sensitive "
"and does not allow wildcard characters."
msgstr ""
"Een kann ok de Funkschoon SEARCH() bruken, man anners as SEARCH() un FIND() "
"passt se op Groot-/Lüttschrieven un op un lett keen Platzhollers to."

#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:9571
#, no-c-format
msgid "FIND(find_text;within_text;start_num)"
msgstr "FIND(Sööktext;binnen_dissen_Text;Startnummer)"

