#. Tag: para
#: functions.docbook:9630
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The FIXED() function rounds a number to the specified number of decimals, "
"formats the number in decimal format string, and returns the result as text. "
"If decimals is negative, number is rounded to the left of the decimal point. "
"If you omit decimals, it is assumed to be 2. If optional parameter no_commas "
"is True, thousand separators will not show up."
msgstr ""
"De Funkschoon FIXED() rundt en Tall na de angeven Tall vun Dezimaalsteden, "
"formateert ehr as en Dezimaalformaat-Tekenkeed un gifft dat Resultaat as "
"Text ut. Wenn \"Dezimaalsteden\" negativ is, warrt de Tall links den "
"Dezimaalpunkt rundt. Ahn \"Dezimaalsteden\" warrt \"2\" vermoodt. Wenn de "
"optschonaal Parameter \"keen_trenntekens\" wohr is, warrt de Dusennerkoppels "
"ahn Trenntekens wiest."

